Be careful on those rocks, Bruce.

120
00:06:39,040 --> 00:06:40,155
It's a dangerous sport.

121
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:44,230
We will, Mr. Fox. We will.

122
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:51,560
Did you know my father was a genius?

123
00:06:52,640 --> 00:06:54,438
He wanted to end fear.

124
00:06:55,680 --> 00:06:56,680
For my sake.

125
00:06:57,320 --> 00:06:58,674
Because he loved me.

126
00:06:59,760 --> 00:07:00,760
So tell me.

127
00:07:01,080 --> 00:07:03,720
What do you fear, Warden?

128
00:07:08,040 --> 00:07:11,715
Something from your childhood, maybe?

129
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:17,392
- (SCREECHING)
- (SCREAMING)

130
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:22,594
Face your fears.

131
00:07:24,200 --> 00:07:28,558
Face your fears and defeat them.

132
00:07:50,880 --> 00:07:51,880
What?

133
00:07:52,240 --> 00:07:53,240
No.

134
