00:35:25,840 --> 00:35:30,471
and actually bulletproof to impacts
from 10 feet or more.

535
00:35:31,320 --> 00:35:32,958
You know, for rock climbing.

536
00:35:34,120 --> 00:35:37,112
Oh, and long-distance
radio communicators.

537
00:35:37,640 --> 00:35:39,631
In case you two wish
to talk to each other

538
00:35:40,960 --> 00:35:41,960
whilst climbing rock.

539
00:35:44,280 --> 00:35:46,840
Well, I will not keep you.

540
00:35:47,640 --> 00:35:50,837
I just didn't want to see you
get hurt again, Mr. Wayne.

541
00:35:53,440 --> 00:35:54,440
Thank you, Mr. Fox.

542
00:35:58,000 --> 00:35:59,229
I feel safer already.

543
00:36:02,760 --> 00:36:06,549
Ladies. Thank you for returning.
I'm glad...

544
00:36:06,640 --> 00:36:07,640
Not so fast.

545
00:36:08,680 --> 00:36:10,591
I'II be needing proof of your sincerity.

546
00:36:11,400 --> 00:36:14,119
Yes. Selena said you would
need something from me.

547
00:36:15,280 --> 00:36:17,351
- You can have anything you like.
- Fine.

548
00:36:18,920 --> 00:36:19,920
I'II take your hand.

549
00:36:21,800 --> 00:36:22,800
My what?

550
00:36:22,920 --> 00:36:26,276
Both Butch and I lost a hand due
to Penguin's Machiavellian war games.

551
00:36:29,920 --> 00:36:31,149
I believe it's your turn.

552
00:36:31,520 --> 00:36:33,591
- You didn't say anything about this.
- Quiet.

553
00:36:33,920 --> 00:36:35,752
- Tabitha, I assure you...
- No more words.

554
00:36:36,640 --> 00:36:39,200
Penguin cut off Butch's hand,
Nygma mine.

555
00:36:41,120 --> 00:36:42,519
Now I take yours.

556
00:36:45,000 --> 00:36:46,000
Fine.

557
00:36:47,120 --> 00:36:49,953
If this is the only way
I can get you to trust me,

558
00:36:54,760 --> 00:36:55,760
so be it.

559
00:37:21,200 --> 00:37:22,200
Fine.

560
00:37:23,200 --> 00:37:24,200
I'II trust you.

561
00:37:25,800 --> 00:37:26,800
For now.

562
00:37:29,880 --> 00:37:30,880
I'II start Monday.

563
00:37:49,560 --> 00:37:50,560
PENGUIN: Where is he?

564
00:37:53,920 --> 00:37:55,479
We had a deal, Detective Gordon.

565
00:37:56,520 --> 00:37:58,955
That you would apprehend Jonathan Crane.

566
00:37:59,440 --> 00:38:01,875
You made a demand
in front of your cronies

567
00:38:02,360 --> 00:38:04,874
in an attempt to undermine
me and this department.

568
00:38:05,360 --> 00:38:06,714
There was no deal.

569
00:38:06,800 --> 00:38:08,677
I spoke for all of
the citizens of Gotham

570
00:38:08,760 --> 00:38:12,390
when I said that the GCPD
can no longer keep us safe.

571
00:38:13,640 --> 00:38:17,793
How many of you are sick
of risking your lives every day

572
00:38:17,880 --> 00:38:19,712
just to see criminals escape?

573
00:38:20,440 --> 00:38:23,637
How many times has this very building
become a war zone?

574
00:38:23,760 --> 00:38:24,760
(INDISTINCT MURMURING)

575
00:38:24,960 --> 00:38:27,349
I say it is time to start anew.

576
00:38:27,760 --> 00:38:31,276
To police ourselves.

577
00:38:32,640 --> 00:38:36,190
I will triple the wage
of any cop here who wants to work for me

578
00:38:36,280 --> 00:38:39,159
in ensuring the safety
of this city's people.

579
00:38:40,000 --> 00:38:41,991
The future is now.

580
00:38:42,760 --> 00:38:44,592
Follow me into it.

581
00:38:46,440 --> 00:38:47,760
Police yourselves.

582
00:38:47,840 --> 00:38:49,990
He just wants to pay you
to look the other way.

583
00:38:50,080 --> 00:38:51,559
Would you blame them if they did?

584
00:38:53,840 --> 00:38:55,800
- I've got nothing to say to you.
- Hey, hey, hey.

585
00:38:56,320 --> 00:38:58,550
This is a war, not one battle.

586
00:38:59,680 --> 00:39:01,910
If I would've went with you,
I would've lost them.

587
00:39:02,800 --> 00:39:04,711
And we need them to win this war.

588
00:39:05,680 --> 00:39:07,353
Now, you don't have to say nothing,

589
00:39:08,160 --> 00:39:09,798
but I am buying you a drink.

590
00:39:24,720 --> 00:39:27,838
Oh, no, not you. Leave!

591
00:39:27,920 --> 00:39:30,070
You never paid
for the last stuff I gave you.

592
00:39:30,600 --> 00:39:34,673
You make me smell perfume.
Make me giddy. Cheap trick!

593
00:39:35,400 --> 00:39:37,038
Out! Out!

594
00:39:37,240 --> 00:39:39,072
I'm done with perfumes.

595
00:39:39,680 --> 00:39:41,000
I'm here for the good stuff.

596
00:39:42,320 --> 00:39:45,199
Don't know what you're talking about.
Leave! I'm closing up.

597
00:39:45,320 --> 00:39:47,197
Word is you have potions here.

598
00:39:48,120 --> 00:39:51,829
Ancient, mystical potions
made by shamans all over the world.

599
00:39:52,680 --> 00:39:53,909
Who told you that?

600
00:39:54,000 --> 00:39:55,320
I'm done playing nice.

601
00:39:55,560 --> 00:39:57,392
I need a change. A big one.

602
00:39:57,480 --> 00:39:59,391
I need strength, power.

603
00:40:00,000 --> 00:40:01,000
No..

604
00:40:01,440 --> 00:40:02,440
Where are they?

605
00:40:03,960 --> 00:40:04,960
My safe.

606
00:40:05,640 --> 00:40:06,640
Under the register.

607
00:40:06,920 --> 00:40:08,593
- Combinationil
- It's open.

608
00:40:14,480 --> 00:40:15,879
Which ones make me stronger?

609
00:40:15,960 --> 00:40:18,998
That's dangerous stuff.
It's too powerful for you.

610
00:40:19,080 --> 00:40:20,912
It can get in your blood, your DNA.

611
00:40:23,280 --> 00:40:24,280
Good.

612
00:40:26,600 --> 00:40:27,600
No!

613
00:40:27,960 --> 00:40:28,960
Stop! No!

614
00:40:29,360 --> 00:40:30,953
No, you must stop!

615
00:40:35,720 --> 00:40:36,720
(PANTING)

616
00:40:50,360 --> 00:40:52,397
You let me walk into
that nightmare alone.

617
00:40:52,480 --> 00:40:53,959
Yeah, well, I figured it would take

618
00:40:54,040 --> 00:40:56,395
more than a couple of loonies
to take you out.

619
00:40:57,160 --> 00:40:59,390
Besides, I figured you and me
taking on Penguin

620
00:40:59,480 --> 00:41:03,030
and the entire criminal underground
by ourselves wasn't the best idea.

621
00:41:03,680 --> 00:41:06,115
So, what, you wanna sit here,
do nothing, get drunk?

622
00:41:06,200 --> 00:41:08,350
- Is that your plan?
- Unless you got a better one.

623
00:41:10,160 --> 00:41:12,720
What makes you think those cops
back there were wrong?

624
00:41:13,720 --> 00:41:15,358
Are we really making a difference?

625
00:41:16,480 --> 00:41:18,039
One worth risking our lives over?

626
00:41:21,520 --> 00:41:23,989
We'd need an army to take on Penguin.

627
00:41:25,640 --> 00:41:26,710
Makes me miss Falcone.

628
00:41:27,280 --> 00:41:31,274
I mean, I know he's a vicious bastard,
but he was... He was fair.

629
00:41:31,960 --> 00:41:34,376
He ran the criminals in this city
with an iron fist. There was...

630
00:41:34,400 --> 00:41:36,232
There was honor.

631
00:41:39,880 --> 00:41:41,473
- No.
- What?

632
00:41:41,600 --> 00:41:43,159
Do not <i>mess</i> with Falcone.

633
00:41:43,320 --> 00:41:47,029
You killed his son, remember?
Italians do not forget that crap.

634
00:41:47,120 --> 00:41:49,555
He must hate what Penguin's doing
as much as we do.

635
00:41:50,400 --> 00:41:52,869
You show your face to Falcone,
he will kill you.

636
00:41:54,560 --> 00:41:55,755
Yeah, well...

637
00:41:58,160 --> 00:42:00,356
Like you said, we need an army.

638
00:42:01,360 --> 00:42:02,360
He's got one.

639
00:42:18,920 --> 00:42:22,470
<i>(OVER RADIO) That's a lovely leap,
Master Bruce. Positively gazelle-like.</i>

640
00:42:22,800 --> 00:42:25,081
It's so lightweight,
it's like I'm wearing nothing at all.

641
00:42:26,640 --> 00:42:27,640
(GRUNTS)

642
00:42:35,080 --> 00:42:37,196
Yeah, well, let's not get ahead
of ourselves.

643
00:42:37,880 --> 00:42:40,156
Remember to keep your face covered
at all times.

644
00:42:41,640 --> 00:42:43,472
<i>Try wearing that mask I made you.</i>

645
00:43:47,920 --> 00:43:48,920
English - SDH

